			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Below are the details to the location of the camp and the tatics/pets used.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Zone:</span> <a href="http://eqatlas.com/ykesha/cryptofnadoxmap.html" target="_blank" class="postlink">Crypt of Nadox</a>
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Camp:</span> NE Caves
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Pet:</span> Ward of Xegony (unfocused)
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Gear:</span> Bazaar geared mage (FT1, 1700hp, 3200 mana pool, SCM 3)
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Specialization:</span> Evocation
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Outside Buffs:</span> KEI
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Respawn Timer:</span> Use Flameshield of Ro (unfocused). After the third flameshield wears off your pet start medding for respawns. Respawn is about 20 minutes.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Experience:</span> About 12-14% AA per a cycle.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Location:</span> This is assuming you know how to get to the lighthouse in Gunthak.Increase your fire resists, invis up and run South out over the water to the beach. Hugging the West wall of the Beach take your first right into the cave. Continue following the cave and take your second left. Take your next right and you will soon zone into Nadox. Once you enter Nadox, run through the lava until you see the bridge overhead. Go up on the ledge just before the bridge. Once you are on solid ground hang a left and follow the lava river (on your left) to the wall. This is 100% safe unless mobs are pulled here. Re-invis here to be on the safe side. Run East past the camp fire and take your second left into the caves. Continue running straight until you hit a dead end. There should be no mobs at this dead end and this will be your camp. This is where you prep and get your pet ready.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Tactic used:</span> 
<br />
1. Pull mob with Malisement
<br />
2. Start casting Fire Bolt of Tallon when mob hits 80%
<br />
3. Start casting Fire Bolt of Tallon when mob hits 40%
<br />
4. Throw in occasional heals as needed. This camp will definitely require more healing than the Furious/Vehement room (Camp 1).
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Mobs:</span>
<br />
