<a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=11206" target="_blank" class="postlink">Foreman Kraksanar</a> (About 12000hp, max hits around 180, enrages)
<br />
.....<span style="font-style: italic">Loot:</span>
<br />
........1. <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=20487" target="_blank" class="postlink">Corroded Pick Hilt</a> 9pp to vendor
<br />
........2. <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=19237" target="_blank" class="postlink">Miner's Pick</a> 5pp to vendor
<br />
........3. Various low end gems between 9pp and 47pp to vendors
<br />
........4. Various research pages and runes
<br />
........5. <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=19981" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ornate Miner's Pick</a> 47pp to vendor
<br />
........6. <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=19203" target="_blank" class="postlink">Steel Wrapped Breastplate</a> Common drop
<br />
........7. <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=19390" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sharpened Bloodtusk Lance</a> Rare drop
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Pulling the camp:</span>
<br />
1. pull the static Troll Quarrier at the bottom of the decline to your camp. This is a place holder for Foreman Kraksanar.
<br />
2. Run to the bottom of the decline and peak around the corner to your right. Pull the mob closest to the camp and against right wall. This is usually a Troll Tunneler but may also be one of the Bloodtusks.
<br />
3. Again, peak around the corner to your right and pull the mob closest to the camp and against the left wall. This is usually a Troll Excavator but may also be one of the Bloodtusks. This is a place holder for the Trench Master.
<br />
4. Peak around the corner to the right and pull the static Troll Quarrier at the top of the hill against the right wall. This is a place holder for Foreman Kraksanar.
<br />
5. Straight ahead of your camp should be a Bloodtusk Boar along the right wall. Pull and kill the boar. This Bloodtusk is the placeholder for the Burdened Bloodtusk. After killing the mob you will see a message about hearing the footsteps or something to that extent. The Burdened Bloodtusk will wander out of the cave to the left and you should be able to pull it safetly back to camp.
<br />
6. Just past the Bloodtusk Boar that was just killed along the right wall is another mob. This is usually a Troll Dredge but may also be one of the Bloodtusks. Pull and kill the mob.
<br />
7. Just past the mob that was just killed along the right wall is another mob. This is usually a Troll Tunneler but may also be one of the Bloodtusks. Pull and kill the mob.
<br />
8. Just past the mob that was just killed on top of the hill and against the left wall is a static Troll Quarrier. This is a placeholder for Foreman Kraksanar.
<br />
9. From the camp, at the bottom of the decline take a left at the interesection. Run a little ways back in the cave and you will find one of the Bloodtusks just over the hill. Pull and kill the Bloodtusk. This Bloodtusk is the placeholder for the Burdened Bloodtusk. After killing the mob you will see a message about hearing the footsteps or something to that extent. The Burdened Bloodtusk will wander out of the cave to the left and you should be able to pull it safetly back to camp.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Special Notes:</span>
<br />
1. Always keep damage shield up on the pet. Remember, this is your respawn timer.
<br />
2. You will complete the cycle before burnout wears off. 
<br />
3. Sometimes when killing the various Trolls, Crew Chief Hanriesaf will spawn on their death. Always be ready for this.
<br />
4. Mobs do not walk when low on hitpoints.
<br />
5. The first round of the cycle is the most mana intensive due to the sheer number of mobs up at that time. This is mostly due to the wandering mobs.
<br />
6. Alter the tactics that would best accomodate your play style. If you are conjuration based Mage healing and conjuration based nukes may be more mana efficient than 2 nukes with Firebolt of Tallon. 
<br />
7. It is a good idea to ensure Malisement lands before nuking. These mobs have decent resists and the mana loss on a resisted nuke can really hurt.
<br />
8. The cycle above does not include the wandering mobs. No wanderer will ever path through your camp but you may need to pull a few wanderers to continue through the above mentioned cycle. There are about 5-6 wanderers that will walk by the intersection just outside the camp.
<br />
9. Eye of Zoom can help scout around the corners. Nothing worse than running around the corner to pull a static spawn and a wanderer is waiting for you.
<br />
10. As you continue through the cycle, periodically check the caves for wanderers headed in your direction. It would be wise to kill them or wait for them to pass. You do not want to be caught in mid pull and have a wanderer aggro you too.
<br />
11. The gear mentioned above is what I had when I started this camp. I have since upgraded a little and it has gotten easier. If you can easily handle the above cycle go a little further in and pull a few more mobs while waiting for respawns.
<br />

<br />
If this walkthrough helps and when time permits I will post other LoY camps for the solo Mage.
<br />

<br />
